<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1742,2020]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1922,1947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species can be recognized by having the embolus extending straight distally and then forming an angle at its middle (
<figureCitation box="[501,580,1958,1983]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) (no abrupt angle in 
<taxonomicName box="[813,908,1960,1983]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[813,908,1960,1983]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">E. igapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[914,1003,1958,1983]" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,1003,1958,1983]" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
; see 
<figureCitation box="[1060,1143,1958,1983]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Also, males of 
<taxonomicName box="[1331,1436,1960,1983]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[1331,1436,1960,1983]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">E. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have smaller terminal apophysis and stronger RTA (
